249	## 5. Theming
250	
251	Three themes shipped: **Editorial Ivory** (default), **Dark**, and **Mono Clean**.
252	
253	Theme tokens in `app/assets/css/tailwind.css` via Tailwind v4 `@theme` blocks. Ivory lives in the base `@theme` block; Dark and Mono Clean live behind `.dark` and `.mono` class selectors applied to `<html>`:
254	
255	```css
256	@import "tailwindcss";
257	
258	@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));
259	
260	@theme {
261	  /* Editorial Ivory (default) */
262	  --color-bg:           oklch(98.5% 0.008 80);
263	  --color-sidebar:      oklch(97.5% 0.008 80);
264	  --color-card:         #ffffff;
265	  --color-border:       oklch(92% 0.012 70);
266	  --color-ink:          oklch(22% 0.02 60);
267	  --color-ink-muted:    oklch(48% 0.015 60);
268	  --color-accent:       oklch(40% 0.09 35);
269	  --color-accent-fg:    oklch(98% 0.005 70);
270	  --font-sans:    "Inter", ui-sans-serif, system-ui;
271	  --font-serif:   "Fraunces", Georgia, serif;
272	  --font-mono:    "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
273	  --radius-card:  10px;
274	}
275	
276	.dark {
277	  --color-bg:           oklch(14% 0.006 240);
278	  --color-sidebar:      oklch(12% 0.005 240);
279	  --color-card:         oklch(19% 0.008 240);
280	  --color-border:       oklch(24% 0.008 240);
281	  --color-ink:          oklch(90% 0.006 240);
282	  --color-ink-muted:    oklch(58% 0.008 240);
283	  --color-accent:       oklch(72% 0.18 200);
284	  --color-accent-fg:    oklch(12% 0.01 240);
285	}
286	
287	.mono {
288	  --color-bg:           oklch(96% 0 0);
